channel.title: Can anyone help me compile on CheezScape v80?
channel.description:
Whenever I try to compile, it gives me the error [CODE] client.java:5147: unreachable statement if(item == 4708 && playerLevel[13] >= 85) ^ Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. 1 error Press any key to continue . . . [/CODE]
It always gives me that error on CheezScape v80 when trying to compile, and then any changes I did to client.java don't end up changing ingame...
Any help?

item.title: Can anyone help me compile on CheezScape v80?
item.dc:creator: @Mr_Waffles Mr. Waffles
item.description:
@Mr_Waffles wrote:

[quote=“Javacisnotrecognized, post:5, topic:25145”]Some people are retards…
Lemme clear this up;
You have an error.[/quote]
By saying some people are retards, I assume you are talking about yourself? I know I have an error, I even said it

Thanks for the information ^^
Now, Is there any help on HOW to fix that error?

I asked if anyone knows how to fix that error…[br][size=1]Posted at: November 13, 2006, 11:45:20 PM[/size][hr][quote=“Sleep, post:4, topic:25145”]Erm… that’s just to compile the server not to run it. Click runserver.bat or something of that sort.[/quote]
And I know that is to compile it…You have to compile it to have the changes you made to the .java file be compiled into a new .class file, so the game reads it…That error stops it from compiling the .java into a .class…[br][size=1]Posted at: November 13, 2006, 11:46:16 PM[/size][hr]Anyone got any info on how to fix this error?
